==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perceptible
<hw>Per*cep"ti*ble</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*s⟦ecr⟧p"t⟦icr⟧*b'l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>perceptibilis</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>perceptible</ets>. See <er>Perceive</er>.]</ety> <def>Capable of
being perceived; cognizable; discernible; perceivable; large enough to
be perceived; not so small as to be incapable of perception.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With a <qex>perceptible</qex> blast of the air.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Per*cep"ti*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Per*cep"ti*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perception</ent>⟦br⟧
